ncy variance) or inconsistent identification of core evidence (high necessity variance). The ultimate goal is to establish a benchmark for evaluating the robustness of interpretability methods—not just against noise, but against benign variations in model realization. This has profound implications for NLP practitioners who rely on explanations for debugging, fairness auditing, and regulatory compliance. A method that fails this stability test cannot be trusted to reveal true model reasoning, regardless of its fidelity or intuitiveness.",
